#### 4.1.3 Quantum Global Attention
Quantum Global Attention methods leverage quantum circuits to perform global mixing across all tokens simultaneously, eschewing the pairwise similarity computations of standard self-attention. Typically, these methods lack an explicit Q⁢K⁢V𝑄𝐾𝑉QKVitalic_Q italic_K italic_V mapping process; instead, they integrate feature mapping and global token mixing within a single parameterized transformation, directly yielding the attention layer’s output. Such approaches often involve specially designed global encoding strategies, enabling efficient information mixing with reduced computational complexity compared to pairwise methods.

